<subSubSection id="C314654B1F605A7DFF7FFC8DFEE5D311" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FFC8DFE67D7D5" blockId="2.[175,781,829,949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
Body brownish, antennae and legs reddish brown, clothed with long, slender, scattered, suberect hairs. Total length 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFE99FC4DFE63D7D5" box="[329,435,925,949]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.45" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="2.45">2.45 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF7166481F605A7DFCB7FC43FA41D7C6" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542012" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3542012" box="[871,1425,915,934]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542012/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" startId="2.[871,940,915,934]" targetBox="[845,1451,189,874]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFCB7FC43FA41D7C6" blockId="2.[871,1425,915,934]" box="[871,1425,915,934]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Figures 4, 5. (4) Metathoracic scent gland. (5) Pygophore.</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FFC0DFE2CD174" blockId="2.[175,782,989,1300]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F605A7DFF7FFC0DFF3AD795" box="[175,234,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13352A451F605A7DFEC4FC0DFEA4D795" box="[276,372,989,1013]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). Slightly granulated, covered with macrochaetae, scattered and slightly curved. Length 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFECDFBCDFE56D055" box="[285,390,1053,1077]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.23">0.23 mm</quantity>
, width across eyes 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFD7EFBCDFCD9D055" box="[686,777,1053,1077]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 mm</quantity>
. Interocular space 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFE73FBECFDDED034" box="[419,526,1084,1108]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.09">0.09 mm</quantity>
. Rostrum reaching second abdominal segment. Antennae (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F605A7DFD71FB8CFCD4D014" box="[673,772,1116,1140]" captionStart="Figures 1–3" captionStartId="1.[175,244,1743,1762]" captionTargetBox="[299,1326,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[296,1330,189,1708]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figures 1–3. (1) Head and thorax, dorsal view. (2) Antennae. (3) Fore wing." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542010/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Figure 2</figureCitation>
) covered with suberect hairs that have the same length as width of antennal segment interspersed with hairs twice the length of width of antennae. Length segment I= 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFE0BFB0CFD94D094" box="[475,580,1244,1268]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.11">0.11 mm</quantity>
; II= 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFD4FFB0CFCD8D094" box="[671,776,1244,1268]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.31">0.31 mm</quantity>
; III= 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFF34FB2CFE9DD174" box="[228,333,1276,1300]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.33">0.33 mm</quantity>
; IV= 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFE5DFB2CFE28D174" box="[397,504,1276,1300]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.37">0.37 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FFAEBFD18D273" blockId="2.[175,781,1339,1555]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F605A7DFF7FFAEBFED8D133" box="[175,264,1339,1363]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum length 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFE2BFAEBFDB4D133" box="[507,612,1339,1363]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.32">0.32 mm</quantity>
; basal width 
<quantity id="4CF69B251F605A7DFF7FFA8BFEDBD113" box="[175,267,1371,1395]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="135" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
. Collar presents in anterior and lateral margins a few long erect hairs. Metathoracic scent gland (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F605A7DFEC0FA4BFEA3D1D3" box="[272,371,1435,1459]" captionStart="Figures 4, 5" captionStartId="2.[871,940,915,934]" captionTargetBox="[845,1451,189,874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[845,1453,189,879]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 4, 5. (4) Metathoracic scent gland. (5) Pygophore." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542012/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Figure 4</figureCitation>
) with anterior branch curved downwards, more developed and raised than posterior branch; the latter slender and directed backwards. Rostral channel faintly developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB136C01F605A7DFF7FF9EBFEE5D311" blockId="2.[175,781,1595,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis id="B97AEAD21F605A7DFF7FF9EBFECED233" box="[175,286,1595,1619]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Pygophore (
<figureCitation id="13352A451F605A7DFE6CF9EBFDCDD233" box="[444,541,1595,1619]" captionStart="Figures 4, 5" captionStartId="2.[871,940,915,934]" captionTargetBox="[845,1451,189,874]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[845,1453,189,879]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figures 4, 5. (4) Metathoracic scent gland. (5) Pygophore." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542012" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542012/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="135">Figure 5</figureCitation>
) narrower than the rest of the abdomen; lateral margins glabrous, posterior margin covered with long, thin, erect hairs interspersed with shorter ones; dorsally at its posterior margin it invaginates and then protrudes as a flat projection; ventrally it forms a uniform lobe. Paramere glabrous, curved, gradually narrows towards the apex which is romus; posterior margin with two lobes at its base, the first more obvious than the second.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
